HEADWORD: Xerophthalmia
<hw>Xe`roph*thal"mi*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
Gr. <?/; <grk>xhro`s</grk> dry + <?/ the eye. See
<er>Ophthalmia</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An abnormal dryness
of the eyeball produced usually by long-continued inflammation and
subsequent atrophy of the conjunctiva.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

